text: Paz Undurraga (June 14, 1930 – August 28, 2019) was a Chilean singer. She began her career as a member of Las Cuatro Brujas, and later became a solo artist. She won the Best Performer Award at the 1989 Viña del Mar International Song Festival. ==References== Category:1930 births Category:2019 deaths Category:Chilean female singers
